value.name: Holding the Baby
value.overview: Holding the Baby is an American sitcom television series that aired from August 23 until December 15, 1998. The series is an American version of the British show of the same name.

value.name: The Baby Huey Show
value.overview: A large, dimwitted baby duck wreaks havoc on those who he comes in contact with as his attempts to help and or play result in hilarious consequences. Huey is often unaware of the havoc he is causing, maintaining an innocence even as a hungry fox attempts - and fails - to eat him.

value.name: The Baby
value.overview: When 38 year-old Natasha is unexpectedly landed with a baby, her life of doing what she wants, when she wants, dramatically implodes. Controlling, manipulative and with violent powers, the baby twists Natasha's life into a horror show. Where does it come from? What does it want? And what lengths will Natasha have to go to in order to get her life back?

value.name: The Boss Baby: Back in Business
value.original_name: The Boss Baby: Back in Business
value.overview: With a little help from his brother and accomplice, Tim, Boss Baby tries to balance family life with his job at Baby Corp headquarters.

value.name: The Baby-Sitters Club
value.overview: In this contemporary take on the beloved book series, five best friends launch a baby-sitting business that's big on fun and adventure.

value.name: The Baby-Sitters Club
value.overview: The Baby-Sitters Club is a 1990 American television series based on Ann M. Martin's children's book series of the same name. The series originally aired on the The Disney Channel, but was also broadcast on HBO and Nickelodeon; all thirteen thirty-minute episodes were also released to home video. The TV series and the novels were both produced by Scholastic Corporation. As of June 1st, 2013, the series was made available on Netflix instant streaming.

value.name: The Return of Superman: Baby Cloud
value.overview: "Baby Cloud" is an original series released on The Return of Superman's official YouTube channel.

value.name: Miss Shachiku and the Little Baby Ghost
value.original_name: 社畜さんは幼女幽霊に癒されたい。
value.overview: From sunup to sundown, Fushihara-san works ’round the clock. She spends so much time there that even the ghosts worry about her well-being! One night, Fushihara-san was working late as usual when a little ghost girl whispered to her, “Leave now”—an encounter that would change her life forever. Be healed by the heartwarming daily life of the cute little ghost and Fushihara-san!

value.name: The Boss Baby: Back in the Crib
value.original_name: The Boss Baby: Back in the Crib
value.overview: Framed for a corporate crime, an adult Ted Templeton turns back into the Boss Baby to live undercover with his brother, Tim, posing as one of his kids.

value.name: The Spoils of Babylon
value.overview: Follow the saga of Cynthia and Devon, two siblings whose intense love drives everything and everyone around them to ruin.

value.name: Bush Baby, Little Angel of the Grasslands
value.original_name: 大草原の小さな天使　ブッシュベイビー
value.overview:
Bush Baby, Little Angel of the Grasslands, shortened as The Bush Baby, is the title of a 1992 anime series consisting of 40, 25-minute episodes. It is based on the novel, The Bushbabies, by Canadian author William Stevenson.

The series is part of Fuji Television & Nippon Animation's World Masterpiece Theater which consists of anime TV series adaptations of classic children's books. It has also been broadcast internationally on networks such as Antena 3, Italia 1, Tele 5, ORF1, ABS-CBN, GMA 7, Quality TeleVision and TVOntario.

value.name: The Yakuza's Guide to Babysitting
value.overview: Kirishima Tooru is as vicious a yakuza as they come, to the point where he's earned the nickname "the Demon of Sakuragi." To get him under control, he's suddenly given a new mission straight from the boss—to babysit his daughter!

value.name: Baby Ballroom: The Championship
value.overview:
Baby Ballroom: The Championship was a dancing show on ITV, which began on Saturday 28 July 2007.

Twelve pairs of juvenile ballroom dancers, aged between six and eleven, competed for the title of Baby Ballroom Champion. The dancers had to impress a panel of three celebrity judges: X Factor's Ray Quinn, former child star Bonnie Langford and famous dance tutor Pierre Dulaine.

Kate Thornton presented the show, where the public decided who went into the final, which was held on Saturday, 11 August. The winners of Baby Ballroom: The Championship were Kim and Josh.

value.name: Daa! Daa! Daa! UFO Baby
value.original_name: だぁ! だぁ! だぁ!
value.overview: Daa! Daa! Daa! UFO Baby is a Japanese children's animated television series produced by J.C.Staff, Directed by Hiroaki Sakurai, and was aired on NHK-BS2 from March 28, 2000 to February 26, 2002.

value.name: Kill Me Baby
value.overview: Kill Me Baby is the touching story of Yasuna, a normal (?) high school girl, and Sonya, her best friend who happens to be an assassin. Unfortunately, little Sonya's trained assassin instincts often work against her and others in her daily high school life, as Yasuna's often-broken wrist can attest to. She just wanted a hug, but she ended up with a broken neck. Isn't it sad? No, it's hilarious.

value.name: Murdered: The Baby on the Beach
value.original_name: Murdered: The Baby on the Beach
value.overview: In the rural Ireland of 1984, the murder of an unidentified infant begins a series of events that eventually shine a spotlight on prejudice, ignorance and police corruption.

value.name: The Baby Borrowers
value.overview:
The Baby Borrowers is an American version of the The Baby Borrowers reality television show based on the British television series of the same name originally aired in 2007. The show features five couples aged between 18 and 20 who either believe that being parents is easy, or are divided upon the issue. They start off attempting to look after a baby for three days, before moving onto toddlers, pre-teens, teenagers and finally an elderly person.

The show is produced by Love Productions, the same company that produces the original British version.

On March 13, 2009, it was confirmed that the series had been canceled and would not be returning for a second season.
